posts.subject: Why isn't there more fed posting
posts.body: We're anonymous enough to have CP spammers. Why not?

I took Ed Dames' LearnRV course. Practiced and did projects for a couple of years. Became fairly decent at it.

Haven't done much with it for a few years. People in the community started chasing after betting associative RV targets. Which doesn't work well as evidenced by the many people trying and the small amount of money made.

There are a lot of different things people call "RV" but for the military/Ingo Swann derived systems it pretty much comes down to: stay in structure.

There are bunches of other systems that are more freeform but I don't know much about those and I haven't done much "psychic" stuff other than LearnRV.

Edit: If you are interested is seeing a CRV type session check out the Companion Guide to Remote Viewing pdf at: http://www.learnrv.com/templates.cfm

It actually has some really good explanation of the process.
